[3] Chile {Chaiten, Los Lagos region]
Date:Mon 26 Sep 2011
Source: BioBio Chile [in Spanish transl., summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2011/09/26/trasladan-a-hombre-supuestamente-afectado-por-el-virus-hanta-hasta-hospital-base-de-puerto-montt.shtml


A man, apparently affected by [a] hantavirus [infection], was taken
from Chaiten to the emergency [unit] of the Puerto Montt Base
Hospital. the patient is a 33 year old man who on Sunday night [25 Sep
2011] was taken from the La Junta area of Chaiten to Puerto Montt
after his hantavirus rapid test was positive.

The man worked in the Los Cisnes community of the La Junta area
previous to 18 Sep [2011] doing tasks in a sawmill 13 km [8 mi] from
the El Amarillo locale in Palena province. During that time, the
patient presented with the 1st symptoms and went to the Futaleufu
Hospital, where the rapid test was done that was positive for
hantaviruses. The Puerto Montt Base Hospital reported that the patient
presented with fever, myalgia, and respiratory complications. However,
despite his serious condition he is stable and out of risk of death.

Statistically, the case corresponds to the Aysen Region and the health
authorities are awaiting the [test] results from the Institute for
Public Health in Santiago to confirm [the diagnosis] of the disease.

We note that the area in the Palena province continues on early,
preventive alert due to the presence of rodents because of the quila
flowering [a perennial bamboo that grows in the humid temperate
forests of Chile and Argentina - Mod.TY] that has caused explosive
reproduction of these mammals [rodents].

communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Although not specified, the hantavirus most likely involved in this
case is Andes virus.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Chaiten in the Los
Lagos region can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1mke. -
Mod.TY]

