[4] Chile (Bio-Bio)
Date: Wed 19 Oct 2011
Source: BioBio Chile [in Spanish transl., summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2011/10/19/detectan-2-nuevos-contagios-de-virus-hanta-en-provincia-de-bio-bio.shtml


The Institute of Public Health today [19 Oct 2011] corroborated 2
hantavirus infections in Bio-Bio province. That brings to 9 registered
cases up to now in the region, 6 of them fatal.

Information from La Radio stated that [the cases] were a 36 year old
woman and a 38 year old man from the Negrette community, where
presumably she was infected while cleaning storage buildings and [he]
canals, respectively, without an epidemiological connection.

Both [patients] were sent to the Los Angeles base Hospital where they
remain in stable condition and have overcome the most critical phase
[of the infection] with a better prognosis, according to information
from the health SEREMI [Secretaria Regional Ministerial de Salud;
government administrative agency]. Luis Hormazabal, in charge of
zoonoses of the health agency, that professionals of this division are
working on the ground to determine the [epidemiological] details of
the infection.

It is worth mentioning that up until now there are 11 confirmed
hantavirus [infection] cases in the region, of which 4 are from
Bio-Bio province. A total of 6 people have died in the area due to
transmission due to this virus transmitted by wild mice.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[These cases are also most likely due to Andes virus infections.

A HealthMap ProMED-mail interactive map of the Bio-Bio region can be
accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/006H. - Mod.TY]

