[5] Argentina ex Chile (Los Rios region): suspected
Date: Sate 15 Oct 2011
Source: BioBio Chile [in Spanish transl., summ. Mod.TY, edited]
http://www.biobiochile.cl/2011/10/15/hasta-neuquen-fue-trasladado-chileno-sospecho-de-portar-virus-hanta.shtml


A 73 year old man from the Pirhuieco frontier locale in Panguipuilli
is currently interned in the intensive care unit of the Neuquen
hospital in Argentina, suspected of having [a] hantavirus infection.
The man was 1st attended to in the San Martin de los Andes medical
center and later taken to Junin and now is located in the intensive
care unit (ICU) in Neuquen. Related tests have been made to determine
the cause of his situation; results are expected within the next 7
days.

The patient cannot be transported to a medical enter in Chile because
the Hua Hum ferry to Panguipuli is under repairs so that the
connection between Pirihueico and Puerto Fey are difficult. [Hua Hum
is an international mountain pass in the Andes and the only connection
here between Chile and Argentina is by ferry across the lake. -
Mod.TY]

The health SEREMI [Secretaria Regional Ministerial de Salud;
governmental administrative unit] is on alert and stated that if other
suspected [hantavirus infection] symptomatic cases present themselves,
they will be sent to Argentina.

--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[These cases are almost certainly due to Andes virus infection.

A map showing the location of the Hua Hum pass can be accessed at
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Huahum_Pass. A HealthMap/ProMED map of
the Los Lagos region can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/18h5.
- Mod.TY]

